channel.title: Unidentified Configuration Files
channel.description:
I'm in the process of converting the 317 cache to a modern format, these files stuck out as not used in the client but they exist in the cache [img]http://i.imgur.com/fE695na.png[/img] Any guesses on what they could be? Edit, attempting to brute force these: There were 6 unknowns, they are param, mesanim, mes. Just appended with 'idx' and 'dat'.
1029250116 MES.DAT -1818025236 PARAM.DAT

item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

seq.dat/idx are used for animations.

I don’t know their exact usage… But I had an older one, and when some animations played (Woodcutting anims, mining anims to name some) it would not remove the weapon I had… But upon going to a newer seq.dat, it fixed this issue.

item.title: Unidentified Configuration Files
item.dc:creator: @silabsoft RuneAgent
item.description:
@silabsoft wrote:

[quote=“sinisoul, post:5, topic:551618”][quote author=Miss Silabsoft link=topic=670532.msg4483644#msg4483644 date=1432276599]
protip the 317 cache is actually 377 its also incomplete because whoever used that particular cache orginally didn’t let the ondemand fetcher finish the idle download of all the cache files.
[/quote]
I noticed there are a lot of missing models, music entries. The unlisted entries are just zeroed out though.[/quote]

If you treat those dat/idx like the others you can read the definition count from the index but when you parse the definition following the same format as all the other configs you will only read opcode 0 for each, opcode 0 indicates end of definition. So if they were used for something realistically we wouldn’t know unless you found a cache that actually contained data.

Read full topic
